######################## --><aside id="upcoming"><h1>Milestones</h1><div class="box"><h1>Lecture </h1><ol class="LecturesLink"><li class="title summary"><a class="url" href="lecture.php?lid=104">CSS: Ch 11, 12, 13</a></li></ol></div><div class="box"><h1>Assignment </h1><ol class="AssignmentLink"><li class="title summary"><a class="url" href="assign.php?pid=25">Style a Table</a> Friday the 20th</li><li class="title summary">Peer Grading <span class="relaseDate">Due Date: 2014-06-05</span> Thursday the 5th</li>
</ol></div><div class="box"><h1>Test </h1><ol class="examLink"><li class="title summary">Exam II Wednesday the 25th</li></ol></div></aside><div id="slide"><h1>Assignment: Redesign the Course Style</h1><h2>DUE: 2015-03-13</h2><h2>Submitted Status: Not submittted.</h2><h2>Category: Homework, Weight: 10%</h2><h2>Group number 12 presenting on Friday March 13 at 3:00</h2><ol class='groupMembers'><li> Lily A. Brown: lbrown20@uvm.edu</li><li> Ryan J. McCague: rmccague@uvm.edu</li><li>Aidan L. Goldman: algoldma@uvm.edu</li></ol><h2>Folder Name: assignment4</h2><p>Link to your assignment (when you have it posted): </p><p class='firstLine'><a href='https://algoldma.w3.uvm.edu/cs142/assignment4/index.php' target='_blank'>https://algoldma.w3.uvm.edu/cs142/assignment4/index.php</a></p> <p>Study the class web sites layout and style sheet. For this assignment you will be creating a new look for the site. You cannot modify the html only the CSS style sheet (w3c.org standards of course). Keep in mind the different devices that we use today (desktop, laptop, tablet, phone etc).</p>

<ol>
    <li>Email your group members and get together to brainstorm ideas and identify strengths and weakness of the group.
    </li>
    <li>Create a drawing of the layout noting the div tags, classes and IDs that you will have access to. You will need to make this drawing an image (post it and submit it) as part of the assignment. Name it: cs142-layout.jpg (you can have more than one drawing, just use a naming convention for ex: cs142-layout-1.jpg). This would be the time to look over the html and if you think you will need any changes present the changes in class before next Friday.</li>
    

    <li>Design your own group look for the site.  Pretty much anything goes, move things around, add backgrounds whatever. I consider this the same as <a target="_blank" href="http://www.csszengarden.com/">CSS Zen Garden</a> only for the class web site. My goal is to collect the designs and allow students to choose whatever design they want. Be sure to name this style sheet <b>algoldma.css</b> each group member should save a copy (they will all look the same).</li>

    <li>Create a print style sheet so your documents look somewhat reasonable printed. Name this style sheet <b>print_algoldma.css</b> each group member should save a copy (they will all look the same).</li>

    <li>Be sure to include links to all files via your main index page. Each group member should have all the files on their site (they will of course be the same files) and each group member will need to submit the assignment.</li>

    <li>There will be class presentations of your design (online: each group will post a screen shot and write a short discussion about the site. The class can then comment on everyones design as if we were in a classroom).</li>

    <li>I will be setting the default CSS to the one you design, till you make one you will have in effect no style sheet. Be sure to place your style sheet so it is accessible by this url:
<br /><br />

<a target="_blank" href="https://algoldma.w3.uvm.edu/cs142/assignment4/algoldma.css">https://algoldma.w3.uvm.edu/cs142/assignment4/algoldma.css</a>
<br /><br />
</li>

<li>The default style sheet can be found here: https://rerickso.w3.uvm.edu/education/blackboard/css/base.css</li>

